            "subtype": "ability",
            "text": "The fulthrethu sustains an *illusory creature* spell. When an *illusory creature* spell is sustained in this way, the illusion isn't automatically destroyed if it's hit by an attack or fails a save. Instead, the fulthrethu takes 3d6 mental damage and must attempt a DC 5 flat check. On a failure, the *illusory creature* spell ends. The fulthrethu can sustain an *illusory creature* spell for up to 8 hours.",
